\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 you're either all in your current relationship or it's taking away from both of you.}{ }
\par\plain 
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 I was\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 not}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~expecting the the insane flood of monkey-brained love chemicals that hit me like an 18-wheeler the next morning. It felt like my entire nervous system had been hijacked; it was somehow intoxicatingly wonderful, and also pants-shittingly terrifying, nauseating and agonizing all at once.}{ }
\par\plain 
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 When I told my friends that I felt like I'd lost my mind, they just laughed. The general response was:\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 "Yep, that's how it's supposed to feel. Welcome to being human. Sucks, doesn't it? It's also great. Congratulations!"}{ }
\par\plain 
\par\plain {If everyone orients their lives around fleeting romantic intensity, then the village will descend into chaos.}
\par\plain 
\par\plain {Temper this passionate thing that lives inside humans. In ancient cultures.}
\par\plain 
\par\plain {Children are negatively affected when one or both parents are destabilized by romantic obsession.}
\par\plain 
\par\plain {Pair bonding is purpose and stability.}
\par\plain 
\par\plain {This dream that we can maintain this elevated euphoric love state for a long period of time. }
\par\plain 
\par\plain {Discipline, Stability, consistency, service to others as core aspects of long term relationships. But people don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t orient their lives around that. They want their heroin. The euphoric highpoint. That is unstable. }
\par\plain 
\par\plain {These people tend to be unhappy.}
\par\plain 
\par\plain {This passionate euphoric high is something they should be expecting and they shouldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t settle for anything less; around their children, she is chasing this thing, that the child can\u8217\'92t give, so the child suppresses emotional needs.}
